{
  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Seed for EtsyMail_OptionSheets collection. Import each top-level key as a document at EtsyMail_OptionSheets/<key>. The sales agent reads from this collection at runtime; this seed is the source of truth.",
    "version": "2.3.1",
    "schemaNotes": [
      "Each product family (huggie, necklace, stud) is one Firestore doc.",
      "sections[] is ordered — agent walks them in that order during spec stage.",
      "Each option has: code, label, priceUsd OR priceQuote (true) OR priceNotAvailable (true), and flag fields.",
      "modifiers[] inside an option override the priceUsd computation (e.g., 'percentOfPair', 'addToTotal').",
      "bulkSavings is the discount tier table — applies to the full per-piece subtotal, then × quantity.",
      "dependencies declare prereqs ('only when chain selected'); the agent skips dependent sections when prereq fails.",
      "unitOfMeasure declares what '1 piece' means (e.g., huggie = pair of 2 charms; stud = pair OR single OR mismatched pair).",
      "escalateOnQuote: true means hitting any priceQuote:true option triggers Needs Review handoff.",
      "Not-available codes (priceNotAvailable:true) cause a hard refusal; the agent must NOT proceed with that selection.",
      "rushProduction is a separate per-order add-on (not a section): $15 flat, regardless of qty. Set globally per family — same policy across all three.",
      "Expedited shipping is read at runtime from EtsyMail_ShippingUpgradesCache (synced from Etsy). The resolver does not embed shipping in the per-piece total."
    ],
    "lastUpdated": "2026-04-26",
    "createdBy": "system:seed",
    "pricingSource": "Updated to match attached Custom Huggie Charm Sheet, Custom Necklace Charm Sheet, and Custom Stud Earring Sheet images exactly."
  },
